      • rbInsert

        private static RedBlackTree<java.lang.Integer> rbInsert(java.io.File rbFile,
                                                        java.lang.Boolean isPrint)
                                                 throws java.io.FileNotFoundException
        Red Black Insert. A method that inserts a certain amount of elements into the red black tree. The method then either prints out the time it took to complete the operations or it doesn't. The method then returns the Red Black Tree with all of the elements that have been inserted.
        Parameters:
        rbFile - the file that contains the inserts
        isPrint - whether or not the times should be printed
        Returns:
        the red black tree with elements inserted
        Throws:
